Date:  30/9/1916
Source:  Stratford Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  7
Edition:
Quote:  A "foxer" is a person who makes a practice of following other people in parks - a prowler... [Counsel] The police seem to have been prowling... [Police Sub- Inspector] It is a case of the foxer foxed.
